overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application to verify its adherence to the Statement of Work and
  detailed specification. The assistant conducted a thorough analysis,
  identifying both successfully implemented features and significant gaps, such
  as the absence of a tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, missing
  COMISA detection, and incomplete Insufficient Sleep Syndrome logic. Following
  this review, a detailed action plan was created. The assistant then proceeded
  to implement the first two high-priority items: integrating a 1-10 tiredness
  severity scale into the questionnaire UI and report, complete with critical
  safety warnings for high scores, and adding explicit detection for Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) in the generated reports. The process
  involved updating types, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic."
